info.description: MPF Monitor (mpf-monitor) ========================= This package is for the Mission Pinball Framework (MPF) Monitor (mpf-monitor). The MPF monitor is a graphical app that connects to a live running instance of MPF and shows the status of various devices. (LEDs, switches, ball locks, etc.). You can add a picture of your playfield and drag-and-drop devices to their proper locations so you can interact with your machine when you're not near your physical machine. The MPF Monitor can run on Windows, Mac, and Linux. It uses PyQt6 (Python bindings for Qt6) for its visual framework. Installation & Instructions --------------------------- Full instructions for installing and using the MPF monitor are included in the MPF documentation here: http://docs.missionpinball.org/en/latest/tools/monitor License ------- * MPF and the MPF Monitor are released under the terms of the MIT License.
